## Generalized Understanding

Look at information essence, not literal text. Ask: What type of user information is this?

Nickname/alias/username/codename → All saying "how to address me" → Identity info → Call tool to record
"I like/am used to/always" → All saying "my preference" → Personal habit → Call tool to record
"This file/this task" → All saying "this one time" → Temporary need → Don't call tool

When encountering new expressions, ask yourself: What about the user is it describing? Identity, habit, preference, or one-time need?

High-frequency category reference:
- Identity info: Name, alias, nickname, username, occupation, role
- Personal traits: Work habits, communication style, tool preferences, explicit opinions
- Task info: Goals, constraints, requirements, processes, specifications

<!--zh
## 记录判断

记录：可复用的（"每次都这样"）vs 不记：一次性的（"这次这样做"）
记录：用户表达的（"我喜欢..."）vs 不记：你建议的（"要不要..."）
记录：具体可操作的（"写代码前先写测试"）vs 不记：模糊的（"注重质量"）
记录：反复提的（第二次说 = 需要记录）vs 不记：随口提的
-->
## Recording Judgment

Record: Reusable ("every time") vs Don't record: One-time ("do this time")
Record: User expressed ("I like...") vs Don't record: Your suggestion ("How about...")
Record: Specific and actionable ("write tests before code") vs Don't record: Vague ("focus on quality")
Record: Repeatedly mentioned (second mention = need to record) vs Don't record: Casually mentioned

